<HL>
   McDonnell Douglas
   Gets Air Force Contract
   Totaling $836.4 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
09/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9
</SO>
<CO>
   MD GM GMH IBM HON LIT
</CO>
<IN>
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<GV>
DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- McDonnell Douglas Corp. received an $836.4
million Air Force contract for F-15E aircraft.
   The F-15E, the company's most sophisticated jet fighter,
has the ability to attack targets on the ground from long
range. Work on the contract is to be completed in May 1992.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   In other awards yesterday, Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of
General Motors Corp., received a $17.4 million Navy contract
for aircraft electronics.
                                                                                                       

   International Business Machines Corp. got a $14.9 million
Navy contract for aircraft electronics.
                                                                                                       

   Honeywell Inc. was given a $13 million Air Force contract
for aircraft navigation equipment.
                                                                                                       

   Litton Systems Inc., a unit of Litton Industries Inc., won
a $12.3 million Air Force contract for aircraft navigation
equipment.
</TEXT>
